<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> get hot • get it hot</xh5><p> <i>get hot—</i>1. begin feeling hot: I would get up and run on the spot. Even when I <u>got hot</u> I continued because I was never so cold in my life. 2. become busy or hectic: Things always <u>get hot</u> around here toward the end of the month.</p><p> <i>get it hot</i>—(coll.) be punished or scolded severely: He’ll <u>get it hot</u> when his mother finds out that he has broken her new vase.</p> </entry>
